<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880303-0138 </DOCNO><HL> Burnham Pacific Plans Stock Swap to Acquire Burnham American </HL><SO> </SO><CO> BPP BMP </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> SAN DIEGO  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Burnham Pacific Properties Inc. and Burnham American Properties Inc. said they agreed to merge the real estate investment trusts in a $15.1 million exchange of stock, leaving Burnham Pacific as the survivor.    Terms call for exchange of all 972,400 shares of Burnham American for 846,000 of Burnham Pacific's 1.5 million shares outstanding. A spokeswoman for the companies, which have the same management, said the merger would increase efficiency of operations. The companies are joint owners of several properties.    Shareholders of both companies will vote at a joint meeting in May, the concerns said.    In composite trading on the American Stock Exchange, Burnham Pacific shares closed at $17.75, unchanged, and Burnham American closed at $15.50, down 25 cents. </TEXT></DOC>